main event: A 12-year-old boy observed a black rectangular object with a bright light in Chicago on 30 January 1963.
interesting points: The sighting lasted for a total of 30 seconds,The object disappeared to the northeast and reappeared at a higher elevation to the northwest,The object was highly maneuverable,The witness described a single bright light preceding the object,The report concluded the sighting as unidentified, with possibilities including a balloon or aircraft.
sighted object: black rectangular object with bright light
